				\begin{document}$$ {K}_{g\left(r,s\right)}=\frac{1}{L}{\displaystyle \sum_{l=1}^L\frac{\left({g}_{l,r}-{p}_l\right)\left({g}_{l,s}-{p}_l\right)}{\left(1-{p}_l\right){p}_l}} $$\end{document}Kgrs=1L∑l=1Lgl,r−plgl,s−pl1−plpl, where L is the number of available SNPs, pl is the allele frequency of the SNP l, and gl,r is the genotype coded as 0, 1, and 2, corresponding to homozygote, heterozygote, and the other homozygote. Here \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
